# Microcredencial: Introducción a la Computación Cuántica

This repository contains educational materials for the microcredential course "Introducción a la Computación Cuántica".

## Content

The repository includes:

- Lecture notes and presentations on quantum computing concepts in the [docs/](docs/) folder.
- Jupyter notebooks with practical implementations and examples of the quantum algorithms in the [algorithms/](algorithms/) folder.
  - [Deutsch-Jozsa Algorithm](algorithms/deutsch_jozsa)
  - [Bernstein-Vazirani Algorithm](algorithms/bernstein_vazirani)

## Requirements

For using the materials in this repository, first clone the repository:

```bash
git clone 
```

Then, create and activate a virtual environment:

```bash
python -m venv venv
```

Finally, install the required packages:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

This way, you will have all the necessary tools to follow along with the implementations provided.
